headline: Dollar Stays Near 3-Month High on Rate-Cut Doubts
summary: The dollar was trading close to a three-month high following a scaling back of U.S. interest-rate cut expectations. In the absence of other major catalysts, markets continue to digest remarks from Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell last week saying a rate cut in December was not a foregone conclusion, Danske Bank's Jens Naervig Pedersen said in a note.

headline: ADP Jobs Report Tops Forecasts, Muddling Fed Outlook; S&P 500 Steady
summary: The report has outsized significance as the government shutdown cancels another Bureau of Labor Statistics jobs report.  S&P 500 futures were little changed, with Advanced Micro Devices falling modestly in reaction to its earnings report.  After Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome Powell insisted that a December rate cut is "far from" a done deal last week, the ADP jobs report will extend the uncertainty.

headline: Wall Street stocks steady after positive jobs data
